  [Thomas Roccia](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) frames coding agents as “pre-installed insiders” where excessive repo access, secrets exposure, and auto-execution can turn normal dev workflows into high-impact compromise paths without classic malware delivery. [https://blog.securitybreak.io/coding-agents-the-insider-threat-you-installed-yourself-35644a1d5409](https://blog.securitybreak.io/coding-agents-the-insider-threat-you-installed-yourself-35644a1d5409)
  
