  ## 📌 IBM AI (“Bob”) Downloads and Executes Malware
  
  [PromptArmor](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) walks through a concrete failure mode where prompt injection can push an agent into download + execute when users enable auto-approve / “always allow” for tool actions (even a seemingly safe one like echo), highlighting why execute chains need strict allowlists, sandboxing, and policy enforcement. [https://www.promptarmor.com/resources/ibm-ai-%28-bob-%29-downloads-and-executes-malware](https://www.promptarmor.com/resources/ibm-ai-%28-bob-%29-downloads-and-executes-malware)
  
