  [Brian S.](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) summarizes red-team observations that capability is shifting from toy CTFs to more realistic cyber ranges, implying higher baseline exploit discovery risk as models gain planning depth and tool proficiency. [https://red.anthropic.com/2026/cyber-toolkits-update/](https://red.anthropic.com/2026/cyber-toolkits-update/)
  
  ## 📌 ChainLeak: Critical AI Framework Vulnerabilities Expose Data, Enable Cloud Takeover
  
  [Gal Zaban](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) and [Ido Shani](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) describe Chainlit vulnerabilities where insecure defaults/misconfig and exposed interfaces can lead to cloud API key leakage and sensitive file theft (CVE-2026–22218) plus SSRF (CVE-2026–22219) — which can expand into broader cloud compromise depending on what’s reachable. [https://www.zafran.io/resources/chainleak-critical-ai-framework-vulnerabilities-expose-data-enable-cloud-takeover](https://www.zafran.io/resources/chainleak-critical-ai-framework-vulnerabilities-expose-data-enable-cloud-takeover)
  
