  ## 📘 The State of Non-Human Identity and AI Security
  
  CSA Oasis survey Aug–Sep 2025 sample 383 finds orgs treat AI identities like NHIs such as service accounts, API keys, chatbots, inheriting credential sprawl and unclear ownership. Biggest gaps include 51% no clear owner, 51% over permissioned access, 49% low visibility, 46% stale or orphaned IDs. Token control lags with 16% not tracking creation and 24% needing over 24h to rotate or revoke after exposure. [https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7422210133281304576](https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7422210133281304576)
  
