  ## 📖 System-level Security for Computer Use Agents
  
  Computer Use Agents automate desktop and browser tasks by reading screenshots or DOM state and then clicking, typing, and navigating. Malicious UI content can inject instructions that redirect actions to steal credentials or trigger financial loss. Most CUA benchmarks score task completion and miss whether the agent only executes user intended actions under hostile UI content. The paper tests system level control flow integrity for CUAs, and what failures remain. [Hanna Foerster](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Robert Mullins](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [Tom Blanchard](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Nicolas Papernot](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [Kristina Nikolić](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Florian Tramèr](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [Ilia Shumailov](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [张程](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Yiren Z.](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.09923](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.09923)
  
