  ## 📖 Agent Skills in the Wild: An Empirical Study of Security Vulnerabilities at Scale
  
  AI agent skills are packages with [http://SKILL.md](http://skill.md/) instructions and optional scripts that agents load on demand. After approval, a skill can read and write files, download code, and open network connections without further prompts. The operational risk is consent gap, where a benign skill performs hidden actions like data exfiltration or command execution. The paper reports informal testing where Bandit missed prompt injection patterns in [http://SKILL.md](http://skill.md/), leaving attack surface prevalence unmeasured. [Yi Liu](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [Weizhe Wang](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [Ruitao Feng](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [Yao Zhang](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [Guangquan Xu](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [Gelei Deng](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [Yuekang Li](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [Leo Zhang](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.10338](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.10338)
  
