  ## 📖 FinVault: Benchmarking Financial Agent Safety in Execution-Grounded Environments
  
  Financial agents powered by LLMs are deployed for investment analysis, risk assessment, and automated decision-making in highly regulated financial environments. The real risk is execution-grounded risks from real operational workflows and state-changing actions. Current safety evaluations largely focus on language-model-level content compliance or abstract agent settings, and infer success based solely on the agent’s textual output. We lack a dedicated end-to-end security evaluation benchmark tailored to the financial sector and closely aligned with actual business processes. [Zhi Yang](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [runguo li](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [强琪琪](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Jiashun Wang](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [娄方淇](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [MENGPING LI](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [程东坡](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Rui Xu](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Heng Lian](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [shuo zhang](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [XiaoLong Liang](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Xiaoming Huang](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [John Wei Zheng](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Zhaowei Liu](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Xin Guo](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Huacan Wang](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [RongHao Chen](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Liwen ZHANG](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.07853](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.07853)
  
  Press enter or click to view image in full size
  
  ![](https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/0*2PU7QwMor1f3ps5W)
  
  ## 📖 Cybersecurity AI: A Game-Theoretic AI for Guiding Attack and Defense
  
  AI-driven penetration testing now executes thousands of actions per hour but still lacks the strategic intuition humans apply in competitive security. To build cybersecurity superintelligence–Cybersecurity AI exceeding best human capability — such strategic intuition must be embedded into agentic reasoning processes. We present Generative Cut-the-Rope (G-CTR), a game-theoretic guidance layer that extracts attack graphs from agent’s context, computes Nash equilibria with effort-aware scoring, and feeds a concise digest back into the LLM loop guiding the agent’s actions. [Víctor Mayoral-Vilches, PhD](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [María Sanz Gómez](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Francesco Balassone](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Stefan Rass](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), Lidia Salas-Espejo, [Benjamin Jablonski](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Luis Javier Navarete](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Maite del Mundo](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) Cristóbal R. J. Veas Chavez1 [https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.05887](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.05887)
  
  Press enter or click to view image in full size
  
  ![](https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/0*C9gEUq4nFEDaxStM)
  
  ## 📖 HoneyTrap: Deceiving Large Language Model Attackers to Honeypot Traps with Resilient Multi-Agent Defense
  
  This work presents HoneyTrap, a proactive deceptive defense for progressively intensifying multi-turn jailbreak attacks. By coordinating four specialized defense agents,HoneyTrap transforms extended adversarial interactions into honeypot-style traps that mislead and drain attacker resources. To assess this paradigm, we introduce the MTJ-Pro benchmark with paired jailbreak and benign dialogues, together with two deception-oriented metrics, MSR and ARC. [Siyuan Li](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), Xi Lin, [Jun W.](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Zehao Liu](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Haoyu Li](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [鞠天杰](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Xiang Chen](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [jianhua liu](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [https://arxiv.org/abs/2601.04034](https://arxiv.org/abs/2601.04034)
  
  Press enter or click to view image in full size
  
  ![](https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/0*lK2zPJmMG_4MQFMh)
  
  ## 📖 Multi-Agent Framework for Threat Mitigation and Resilience in AI-Based Systems
  
  Machine learning (ML) underpins foundation models in finance, healthcare, and critical infrastructure, making them targets for data poisoning, model extraction, prompt injection, automated jailbreaking, and preference-guided black-box attacks that exploit model comparisons. Larger models can be more vulnerable to introspection-driven jailbreaks and cross-modal manipulation. Traditional cybersecurity lacks ML-specific threat modeling for foundation, multimodal, and RAG systems. Objective: Characterize ML security risks by identifying dominant TTPs, vulnerabilities, and targeted lifecycle stages. [Armstrong Foundjem](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Lionel T., Ph.D](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Léuson Da Silva](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Foutse Khomh](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.23132](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.23132)
  
  Press enter or click to view image in full size
  
  ![](https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/0*lMl-aq_slEXJPpdo)
  
  ## 📖 It’s a TRAP! Task-Redirecting Agent Persuasion Benchmark for Web Agents
  
  We introduce TRAP, a benchmark for systematically evaluating persuasion-driven prompt injection attacks against LLM-based web agents operating in realistic environments. As agents process web content directly, attackers can hide harmful instructions within ordinary webpage elements, making them difficult to detect. When executed, these instructions can redirect agents from their intended tasks, leak sensitive data or cause financial and reputational damage. [Karolina Korgul](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Yushi Yang](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [Arkadiusz Drohomirecki](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [Piotr Błaszczyk](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) Will Howards [Lukas Aichberger](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#), [Chris Russell](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [Ethan (Philip) H. SEOW 萧鸿业](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [Adel Bibi](https://www.linkedin.com/article/edit/7421868819025059841/#) [https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.23128](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.23128)
  
